During a teleconference in the Roosevelt Room, President Biden spoke with Dr. Watkins and Dr. Mohan from NASA's Jet Propulsion Laboratory (JPL) to express his gratitude and admiration for their successful Mars landing mission with the Perseverance rover. The President commended the team for their hard work and dedication, stating that they had restored confidence in the American people and demonstrated the American spirit. He emphasized the importance of science, diversity, and the ability to overcome challenges, mentioning that their achievement would inspire future generations. President Biden also highlighted the significance of America's image in the world and the need for democracies to prove their efficiency. He thanked the team for their contributions and expressed his pride in their accomplishments. The President concluded the conversation by expressing his eagerness to meet the team in person and thanking them once again.